Common.LongDescription.Common.Text: Dakota Business Park is located just off Speke Boulevard within South Liverpool's burgeoning business community.Â  The New Mersey Shopping Park is close by with occupiers such as Next, Boots, McDonalds and Marks & Spencer.

Mersey House, built in 1918, has a wealth of original character including feature fireplaces in most rooms and ornate covings. Matchworks also has easy access to the motorway network with the M57, M62 and M56 all close by. Liverpool John Lennon Airport is less than two minutes drive away and Liverpool South Parkway station is within walking distance.

Self contained lower ground floor units are available at the Matchworks offering a mixture of specification including fully fitted out offices with raised floor, suspended lighting with kitchen and toilet facilities. Alternatively units are available as a shell or can be fitted out bespoke for a variety uses, inclusive car parking provided.

The property is situated in a highly prominent position on the easterly side of the New Chester Road (A41) less than one mile from Birkehead town centre. The A41 is the main arterial route from Birkenhead to Chester and North Wales.

Free car parking is available and the business park has its own railway station and good on-site amenities including Coffee Union.

Sitting proudly at the corner of Paddington Village, Liverpoolâs new flagship building, The Spine, demonstrates our ambition to make KQ Liverpool a world-leading innovation district. The 14-storey, 160,000 sq ft building will not only be BREEAM Excellent rated but will also be one of the first in the UK designed to achieve a WELL Standard Certification â making it one of the best working environments for mental health and physical wellbeing. Using a biophilic design â an innovative way of designing the places in which we live, work and learn â The Spineâs timber curtain wall system and unique ceramic frit facade, reconnects people with nature, creating a healthier environment that is proven to help productivity. The ceramic frit facade, complete with 23 million unique voronoi polygons that mimic human skin, wraps the building and reacts to the local environment, reducing glare and noise. Affectionately named after the striking staircase that runs up the north elevation of the building, The Spineâs lower and upper floors will be occupied by the prestigious Royal College of Physicians, who are opening their new Northern Centre of Excellence in summer 2020, with the remainder of the building available to pre-let to other health, science and education occupiers.

Today it's a precious Grade I listed gem at the centre of Liverpool's business district, giving you and your staff a base full of Victorian character and access to all the modern amenities of the city.
